Cuban Government Charges U.S. for Bomb Blasts 
The Cuban government charged today the United States with being
responsible for a series of bomb attacks against tourism hotels
occurred in the island.
On Thursday, there were four detonations in four tourism hotels in
Havana, that killed an Italian businessman.
Foreign Affairs Minister Roberto Robaina said the Cuban government has
all the evidence to prove that these activities were organized and
directed from the U.S.
He warned that it will not permit anything to disturb the peace and
security of Cuba.
